(252, 2, '2019-05-24 06:04:04', '2019-05-24 06:04:04', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The Yandhai Nepean Crossing is a new pedestrian and cyclist bridge that spans the Nepean River between Penrith and Emu Plains. It was officially opened in October 2018.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":253,\"align\":\"center\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter\"><img src=\"https://sydneytimbersolutions.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/nepean-river-bridge-16.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-253\"/></figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>During construction phase, it became evident that the timber features being installed (which had not yet been treated), were leaching and staining the surrounding areas.It was at this point, that engineers on the project engaged Sydney Timber to come up with a solution. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":254,\"align\":\"center\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter\"><img src=\"https://sydneytimbersolutions.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/example-of-leaching.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-254\"/><figcaption>An example of timber leaching into the surrounding concrete.</figcaption></figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In collaboration with site engineers, we tested a range of possible solutions to ensure the best solution was deployed. The project was then carried out in two phases concurrently. The timber that was already installed was rectified on site, whilst the uninstalled timbers were delivered to our factory for treatment. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":240,\"align\":\"center\",\"width\":512,\"height\":384} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter is-resized\"><img src=\"https://sydneytimbersolutions.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/Penrith-Bridge-1-1024x768.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-240\" width=\"512\" height=\"384\"/><figcaption>The bridge in construction phase.</figcaption></figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":239,\"align\":\"center\",\"width\":384,\"height\":512} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter is-resized\"><img src=\"https://sydneytimbersolutions.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/Penrith-Bridge-2-e1558672658458-768x1024.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-239\" width=\"384\" height=\"512\"/></figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In both cases, the timbers were first washed with an alkaline solution to draw the tannins out. They were then treated with Cutek Extreme, to ensure the timber was sufficiently protected from its highly exposed future environment. The timbers were coated in clear oil without tint, allowing the timber to naturally silver over time.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":238,\"align\":\"center\",\"width\":384,\"height\":512} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter is-resized\"><img src=\"https://sydneytimbersolutions.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/Penrith-Bridge-3-e1558672674812-768x1024.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-238\" width=\"384\" height=\"512\"/></figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":237,\"align\":\"center\",\"width\":384,\"height\":512} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter is-resized\"><img src=\"https://sydneytimbersolutions.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/Penrith-Bridge-4-e1558672689549-768x1024.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-237\" width=\"384\" height=\"512\"/><figcaption>We also installed slip safe grip on some of the timber features to adhere to safety regulations.</figcaption></figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Sydney Timber were proud to be present at the grand opening of the bridge by state premier, the Hon Gladys Berejiklian MP, Premier of New South Wales, and the Hon Stuart Ayres MP, Member for Penrith. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The new bridge continues to be a source of pride for the local community.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Project | Yandhai Nepean Crossing, Penrith', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'project-yandhai-nepean-crossing-penrith', '', '', '2019-05-24 06:04:04', '2019-05-24 06:04:04', '', 0, 'https://sydneytimbersolutions.com.au/?page_id=252', 0, 'page', '', 0),
