(391, 2, '2019-06-11 05:33:40', '2019-06-11 05:33:40', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The Connection is a&nbsp;community facility located on the Rhodes foreshore. It caters for a wide range of functions and events.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>This facility was originally <a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https://sydneytimbersolutions.com.au/pre-coating/\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>pre-coated</strong></a> using <a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https://sydneytimbersolutions.com.au/cutek/\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Cutek</strong></a> so this was purely a maintenance job to freshen up the timber cladding on the buildings as well as the timber decks.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>All timber surfaces were washed thoroughly using Cutek Proclean and then coated with Cutek Extreme, using a Sela Brown colourtone. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>This maintenance job was a simple process due to the initial investment in <a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" aria-label=\"pre-coating (opens in a new tab)\" href=\"https://sydneytimbersolutions.com.au/pre-coating/\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>pre-coating</strong></a> the timber and using <a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" aria-label=\"Cutek (opens in a new tab)\" href=\"https://sydneytimbersolutions.com.au/cutek/\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Cutek</strong></a>. &nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":385} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://sydneytimbersolutions.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/The-Connection-3.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-385\"/><figcaption>One of the Connection buildings, prior to maintenance.</figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":384} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://sydneytimbersolutions.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/The-Connection-4.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-384\"/><figcaption>The same area after we had cleaned and applied Cutek oil. </figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":382} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://sydneytimbersolutions.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/The-Connection-1.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-382\"/><figcaption>A \"mid-maintenance\" picture that demonstrates the before and after. </figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":386} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://sydneytimbersolutions.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/The-Connection-2.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-386\"/><figcaption>Another area of the Connection, prior to maintenance.</figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":389} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://sydneytimbersolutions.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/The-Connection-5.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-389\"/><figcaption>The outside of a seating area in The Connection, post maintenance. </figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->', 'The Connection, Rhodes', 'The Connection is a community facility located on the Rhodes foreshore. The timber elements were originally pre-coated so this was a simple maintenance job to freshen up the cladding and decks.', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '340-revision-v1', '', '', '2019-06-11 05:33:40', '2019-06-11 05:33:40', '', 340, 'https://sydneytimbersolutions.com.au/340-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(392, 2, '2019-06-11 05:37:55', '2019-06-11 05:37:55', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>This building was originally a series of terraces that were converted into one large commercial premise. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>During construction phase much of the timber was exposed. The chosen timber (laminated beams) was never intended to be subject to external weather conditions, however due to the time lapse between initial construction and the roof finally going on, the timber had weathered significantly. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>For this project, all of the timber was thoroughly sanded, and then coated with Cutek Extreme. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":302} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://sydneytimbersolutions.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Elizabeth-St-Paddington-7.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-302\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":296} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://sydneytimbersolutions.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Elizabeth-St-Paddington-3.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-296\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":297} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://sydneytimbersolutions.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Elizabeth-St-Paddington-1.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-297\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":299} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://sydneytimbersolutions.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Elizabeth-St-Paddington-4.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-299\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":301} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://sydneytimbersolutions.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Elizabeth-St-Paddington-6.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-301\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":300} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://sydneytimbersolutions.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Elizabeth-St-Paddington-5.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-300\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":298} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://sydneytimbersolutions.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Elizabeth-St-Paddington-2.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-298\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->', 'Retail/Commercial Building, Paddington', 'This building was originally a series of terraces that were converted into one large commercial premise. The timber features which are all internal, were exposed during construction, so we had to sand and coat the timber in order to restore it to it\'s original condition. ', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '295-revision-v1', '', '', '2019-06-11 05:37:55', '2019-06-11 05:37:55', '', 295, 'https://sydneytimbersolutions.com.au/295-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(393, 2, '2019-06-11 05:41:30', '2019-06-11 05:41:30', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The Yandhai Nepean Crossing is a new pedestrian and cyclist bridge that spans the Nepean River between Penrith and Emu Plains. It was officially opened in October 2018. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":240} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://sydneytimbersolutions.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/Penrith-Bridge-1-1024x768.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-240\"/><figcaption>The bridge in construction phase.</figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":239} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://sydneytimbersolutions.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/Penrith-Bridge-2-e1558672658458-768x1024.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-239\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":238} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://sydneytimbersolutions.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/Penrith-Bridge-3-e1558672674812-768x1024.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-238\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p> <strong>The brief:</strong>To ensure all timber features of this newly built bridge were treated and protected. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>During construction phase, it became evident that the timber features being installed (which had not yet been treated), were leaching and staining the surrounding areas.&nbsp;It was at this point, that engineers on the project engaged Sydney Timber to come up with a solution. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":254,\"align\":\"center\",\"width\":577,\"height\":295} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter is-resized\"><img src=\"https://sydneytimbersolutions.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/example-of-leaching.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-254\" width=\"577\" height=\"295\"/><figcaption>An example of timber leaching into the surrounding concrete.</figcaption></figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>\n\nIn collaboration with site engineers, we tested a range of possible solutions to ensure the best solution was deployed. The project was then carried out in two phases concurrently. The timber that was already installed was rectified on site, whilst the uninstalled timbers were delivered to our factory for treatment.\n\n</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In both cases, the timbers were first washed with an alkaline solution to draw the tannins out. They were then treated with Cutek Extreme, to ensure the timber was sufficiently protected from its highly exposed future environment. The timbers were coated in clear oil without tint, allowing the timber to naturally silver over time.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":237,\"align\":\"center\",\"width\":384,\"height\":512} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter is-resized\"><img src=\"https://sydneytimbersolutions.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/Penrith-Bridge-4-e1558672689549-768x1024.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-237\" width=\"384\" height=\"512\"/><figcaption>We also installed slip safe grip on some of the timber features to adhere to safety regulations.</figcaption></figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Sydney Timber were proud to be present at the grand opening of the bridge by state premier, the Hon Gladys Berejiklian MP, Premier of New South Wales, and the Hon Stuart Ayres MP, Member for Penrith. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The new bridge continues to be a source of pride for the local community.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:shortcode -->\n[SLGF id=291]\n<!-- /wp:shortcode -->', 'Yandhai Nepean Crossing, Penrith', 'The Yandhai Nepean Crossing is a new pedestrian and cyclist bridge that spans the Nepean River between Penrith and Emu Plains. It was officially opened in October 2018. ', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '268-revision-v1', '', '', '2019-06-11 05:41:30', '2019-06-11 05:41:30', '', 268, 'https://sydneytimbersolutions.com.au/268-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
